HEADWORD: Gravid
<hw>Grav"id</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>gravidus</ets>, fr. <ets>gravis</ets> heavy, loaded. See
<er>Grave</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <def>Being with child; heavy with
young; pregnant; fruitful; <as>as, a <ex>gravid</ex> uterus;
<ex>gravid</ex> piety</as>; -- of animals as well as people.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧ His <xex>gravid</xex> associate.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Sir T.
Herbert.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

